originalText.text: Inwood Heights Inc. changed the entry lobby/basement entrance key without advance notice or warning. Did not have enough copies to give out to tenants. Did not have clear oversight of the change, Has limited tenant to have solely 1 physical copy of the new card key and 1 cellular device access despite apartment housing 4 people. This is unsafe to do without notice. 2 weeks later and we have yet to receive formal instructions on how to move forward with this matter. Neither have we received a privacy policy of some kind about the App they have decided to partner with.
